July 2008

same JRE version for license server and ASIPmeister

Test 2: Installation on Centos 5 Machine with the same Floating License
=======================================================================
I think CentOS is very similar to redhat OS, and CentOS 4 or 5
is good environment for ASIP Meister.
We are sorry we have never checked whether ASP Meister run or
does not run on debian derivative
Furthermore, Java environment is very sensitive to its version, it is not
always upper compatible. Please use attached jre (JRE for 32 bit
reahat linux system).
Oops, file is too large to be attached.
-- 20MB
jre-6u45-linux-i586-rpm.bin
--
Can you down load the above file from the following URL
http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/java-archive-downloads-javase6-419409.html

Yoshinori Takeuchi

 CentOS 6 or 7 is not appropriate selection for ASIP Meister.

Yoshinori Takeuchi

you have already set up 32-bit centOS 5 environment for

with/without backslash "/" at the end of path.

After that, if your situation does not change, we should separate
the reason of the problem, licensing or main program.

jre-6u45-linux-i586-rpm.bin.

which runs on 32-bit centOS 5 environment.

Test 3: Installation on Centos 5 Machine with Node License
======================================================
Step 3. Installing Application Program Development Environment Generation Tools
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 3-1. Preparing for Installation
------------------------------------
I have copied tools to /AM/AM_tools directory. The ASIPmeister is in /AM/ASIPmeister directory.

[root@i80pc57 ~]# ls /AM/
AM_tools  ASIPmeister
[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# ls
binutils-2.16.1  binutils-2.16.1.tar.bz2  gcc-4.2.2  gcc-4.2.2.tar.bz2  gdb-6.4  gdb-6.4.tar.gz  Makefile.APDEV  meister  newlib-1.14.0  newlib-1.14.0.tar.gz
[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# 

Then setting some paths as follows:

[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# export ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT=/AM/AM_tools
[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# export ASIPmeister_HOME=/AM/ASIPmeister

Step 3-2. Installing the application program development environment generation tools
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# make -f Makefile.APDEV 
tar xjf binutils-2.16.1.tar.bz2 -C /AM/AM_tools
tar xzf gdb-6.4.tar.gz -C /AM/AM_tools
tar xjf gcc-4.2.2.tar.bz2 -C /AM/AM_tools
tar xzf newlib-1.14.0.tar.gz -C /AM/AM_tools
patch -p0 -d /AM/AM_tools/binutils-2.16.1 < /AM/ASIPmeister/share/patch/binutils-2.16.1-brownie32std-20080711.patch
patching file config.sub
....
patch -p1 -d /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0 < /AM/ASIPmeister/share/patch/newlib-1.14.0-missing-makeinfo.patch
patching file configure
Hunk #1 succeeded at 3545 (offset 3 lines).
[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# make -f Makefile.APDEV install
make: *** Keine Regel, um »install« zu erstellen.  Schluss.

export ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT=/AM/AM_tools
export ASIPmeister_HOME=/AM/ASIPmeister

Dear Hussain,
Do you use SELinux? If so, please stop SELinux.
Other reason is that ASIP Meister uses /tmp dir temporarily.
Please check whether you can write and delete some files into /tmp directory.
Root user is not good for normal use. Please use another general
user.
Yoshinori Takeuchi

Dear Hussain,
I am not sure SElinux affets the ASIP Meister behavior.
But, from my experience, many softwares do not run on SElinux.
Disabling SElinux is good idea to check the system.
Current version ASIP Meister does not use fhm_server, so it is
not required in the system.
Could you check libcrypto library in your system?
Could you run the following commands?
$ cd /lib
$ ls libcrypto*
According to some installation options, libcrypto library seems
not be installed in the system. ASIP Meister uses libcrypto
library to start for license checking.
libcrypto.so.4
Could you install the libcrypto library in the following command,
and start gain ASIP Mester?
$ yum install /lib/libcrypto.so.4
Best regards,
Yoshinori Takeuchi


Dear Professor,
I think libcrypto is already installed as indicated by:
[root@i80pc57 ~]# whereis libcrypto.so.4
libcrypto.so: /lib/libcrypto.so.6
[root@i80pc57 ~]# cd /lib
[root@i80pc57 lib]# ls libcrypto*
libcrypto.so.0.9.8e  libcrypto.so.6
[root@i80pc57 lib]#
But, its libcrypto.so.6  not libcrypto.so.4, does it matter?
While trying to yum install /lib/libcrypto.so.4 gives the following error:
[root@i80pc57 lib]# yum install /lib/libcrypto.so.4
Loaded plugins: fastestmirror
Loading mirror speeds from cached hostfile
...
No Match for argument: /lib/libcrypto.so.4
No package /lib/libcrypto.so.4 available.
Nothing to do
[root@i80pc57 lib]# 
I could not install libcrypto.so.4 as, I think libcrypto.so.6 is also there and which is indicated by  whereis libcrypto.so.4
Is it sufficient for the ASIPmeister to run?
BR, Sajjad


Dear Hussain,
Could you type the following command?
$ ls -l libcrypto*
I think you get the following results.
---
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 1156676  6月  5  2014 libcrypto.so.0.9.7a
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 1300836  5月 31  2016 libcrypto.so.0.9.8e
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root      19  4月 13 09:36 libcrypto.so.4 -> libcrypto.so.0.9.7a
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root      19  9月 30  2016 libcrypto.so.6 -> libcrypto.so.0.9.8e
----
ASIP Meister requires libcryptocd.so.4. If you don't have libcrypto.so.4,
please type the following command.
$ sudo ln -s libcrypto.so.0.9.8e libcrypto.so.4
Then restart again.
Thank you again for your cooperation.
Yoshinori Takeuchi


Dear Hussain,
No, librcypto.so.6 does not become automatical replacement of
libcrypto.so.4. You should explicitly make libcrypto.so.4.
Please use the following command,
$ sudo ln -s libcrypto.so.0.9.8e libcrypto.so.4
Real library is libcrypto.so.0.9.8e, and it should be
symbolically linked to libcrypto.so.4.
Therefore, system recognizes it libcrypto.so.4.
Best regards,
Yoshinori Takeuchi


Dear Professor,
1. Yes, It works fine now, after issuing:
$ cd /lib
$ sudo ln -s libcrypto.so.0.9.8e libcrypto.so.4
Thanks a lot for your helo through out the process.
2. Can we now try to install the ASIPmeister on our servers with floating License? 
Should we use the same Floating License files?

Sajjad

Dear Hussain,
Sorry for late reply. I skipped your question about compiler system.
Current compiler is just for brownie 32-bit processor, and please
think it is beta release.
I am sorry to say that system cannot generate a compiler for
samall_RISC processor. Please do not use compiler for small_RISC.
Only brownie processor is supported.
From my memory, all GNU tools should be patched by supplement programs
for browine 32 before use, which is included in brownie package.
You need gcc to compile target gcc-4.2.2 for brownie processor.
From Compiler Generation error, there is no PATH to use gcc.
Please add path to use gcc on the system.
Your system seems to be 64 bit because i686-pc-linux-gnu is
appeared checking host system type. It is OK?
Yoshionri Takeuchi


Dear Professor,
Yes, I found that its only for the brownie processor. But, In my case it gave the same error while generate the compiler for the brownie processor.
1. All the patch work is already done for this version. As mentioned in AM234STDLIN/package/README_en.txt that:
1. FHM Installation
    * FHM for Brownie is pre-installed on ASIP Meister Std 2.3, this section 
     on the FHM installation can be skipped. 
Isn't it?
2. Should I install gcc separately? Because I thought Makefile.APDEV has already installed AM_STD_234-2/gcc-4.2.2.
BR, Sajjad


Dear Hussain,
Patch seems to be processed correctly.
> 2. Should I install gcc separately? Because I thought Makefile.APDEV has
> already installed AM_STD_234-2/gcc-4.2.2.
>
Yes. You need gcc (host compiler) to compile AM_STD_234-2/gcc-4.2.2 (target compiler).
gcc-4.2.2 for intel is preferable version to be used.
gcc from version 5 has been strongly changed.
I think gcc version 4 is installed on CentOS 5.
Best regards,
Yoshinori Takeuchi




GCC Problem:
-----------------

Dear Professor,
Thanks a lot. We are using CentOS 5, but there is no GCC included, meanwhile we tried to install GCC-4.xx but could not succeed as these libraries are no more available. We just want to know that can we use CentOS-6 or CentOS-7 as these operating systems have recent repositories?
BR, Sajjad


Dear Dussain,
I am sorry to hear your situation and to say that
CentOS 6 or 7 is not appropriate selection for ASIP Meister.
As you said, installing new gcc system is not easy, because
gcc requires very strict version dependency on gnu tools
softwares and OS.
From my experience, when installing a new OS for developers,
gcc is automatically included in the system after OS installation.
It means that you select developers when installing centOS.
Best regards,
Yoshinori Takeuchi


Dear Professor,
I discussed it with our technicians who installed CentOS-5. Actually, the gcc repositories from CentOS Server are removed and we are not able to install it (Development Tools) even during the CentOS-5 fresh installation. Also CentOS-4 don't have all the repositories.

[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# cat ./Makefile.APDEV 

# Copyright (C) 2009 ASIP Solutions, Inc. All rights reserved.

### varible definition

# if non-definition of ASIPmeister_HOME, set
#ASIPmeister_HOME ?= /usr/local/ASIPmeister
ASIPmeister_HOME=/AM/ASIPmeister
ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT=/AM/AM_tools

# directory name
BINUTILS = binutils-2.16.1
GCC = gcc-4.2.2
GDB = gdb-6.4
NEWLIB = newlib-1.14.0

# directory path
# ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT has been already defined by user
BINUTILSDIR = $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)/$(BINUTILS)
GCCDIR = $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)/$(GCC)
GDBDIR = $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)/$(GDB)
NEWLIBDIR = $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)/$(NEWLIB)

# patch path
PATCHDIR = $(ASIPmeister_HOME)/share/patch
BINUTILSPATCH1 = $(PATCHDIR)/binutils-2.16.1-brownie32std-20080711.patch
BINUTILSPATCH2 = $(PATCHDIR)/binutils-2.16.1-ccg-brownie32std-20081222.patch
GDBPATCH1 = $(PATCHDIR)/gdb-6.4-brownie32std-20080711.patch
GDBPATCH2 = $(PATCHDIR)/gdb-6.4-ccg-brownie32std-20081222.patch
GCCPATCH = $(PATCHDIR)/gcc-4.2.2-brownie32std-20080225.patch
NEWLIBPATCH1 = $(PATCHDIR)/newlib-1.14.0-brownie32std-20080225.patch
NEWLIBPATCH2 = $(PATCHDIR)/newlib-1.14.0-missing-makeinfo.patch

# configure and make 
MAKE = make

# make install archc and copy xerces library file
INSTALL = make install
ASIPMEISTERLIB = $(ASIPmeister_HOME)/lib

# others
TAR = .tar.gz
BZ2 = .tar.bz2



### make
default:
# extraction
	tar xjf $(BINUTILS)$(BZ2) -C $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)
	tar xzf $(GDB)$(TAR) -C $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)
	tar xjf $(GCC)$(BZ2) -C $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)
	tar xzf $(NEWLIB)$(TAR) -C $(ASIP_APDEV_SRCROOT)

# patch
	patch -p0 -d $(BINUTILSDIR) < $(BINUTILSPATCH1)
	patch -p1 -d $(BINUTILSDIR) < $(BINUTILSPATCH2)
	patch -p0 -d $(GDBDIR) < $(GDBPATCH1)
	patch -p1 -d $(GDBDIR) < $(GDBPATCH2)
	patch -p0 -d $(GCCDIR) < $(GCCPATCH)
	patch -p0 -d $(NEWLIBDIR) < $(NEWLIBPATCH1)
	patch -p1 -d $(NEWLIBDIR) < $(NEWLIBPATCH2)

[root@i80pc57 AM_tools]# make -f Makefile.APDEV install
make: *** No rule to make target `install'.  Stop.

restore=: && backupdir=".am$$" && \
	am__cwd=`pwd` && cd ../../../bfd/doc && \
	rm -rf $backupdir && mkdir $backupdir && \
	if (makeinfo --split-size=5000000 --version) >/dev/null 2>&1; then \
	  for f in ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info-[0-9] ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info-[0-9][0-9] ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.i[0-9] ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.i[0-9][0-9]; do \
	    if test -f $f; then mv $f $backupdir; restore=mv; else :; fi; \
	  done; \
	else :; fi && \
	cd "$am__cwd"; \
	if makeinfo --split-size=5000000   -I ../../../bfd/doc \
	 -o ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.texinfo; \
	then \
	  rc=0; \
	  cd ../../../bfd/doc; \
	else \
	  rc=$?; \
	  cd ../../../bfd/doc && \
	  $restore $backupdir/* `echo "./../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info" | sed 's|[^/]*$||'`; \
	fi; \
	rm -rf $backupdir; exit $rc

restore=: && backupdir=".am$$" && \
	am__cwd=`pwd` && cd ../../../gas/doc && \
	rm -rf $backupdir && mkdir $backupdir && \
	for f in ../../../gas/doc/as.info ../../../gas/doc/as.info-[0-9] ../../../gas/doc/as.info-[0-9][0-9] ../../../gas/doc/as.i[0-9] ../../../gas/doc/as.i[0-9][0-9]; do \
	  if test -f $f; then mv $f $backupdir; restore=mv; else :; fi; \
	done; \
	cd "$am__cwd"; \
	if makeinfo --split-size=5000000   -I ../../../gas/doc \
	 -o ../../../gas/doc/as.info ../../../gas/doc/as.texinfo; \
	then \
	  rc=0; \
	  cd ../../../gas/doc; \
	else \
	  rc=$?; \
	  cd ../../../gas/doc && \
	  $restore $backupdir/* `echo "./../../../gas/doc/as.info" | sed 's|[^/]*$||'`; \
	fi; \
	rm -rf $backupdir; exit $rc

	    /usr/bin/install -c -m 644 $h ${thd}; \
	  done; \
	fi

restore=: && backupdir=".am$$" && \
	am__cwd=`pwd` && cd ../../../bfd/doc && \
	rm -rf $backupdir && mkdir $backupdir && \
	if (makeinfo --split-size=5000000 --split-size=5000000 --version) >/dev/null 2>&1; then \
	  for f in ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info-[0-9] ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info-[0-9][0-9] ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.i[0-9] ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.i[0-9][0-9]; do \
	    if test -f $f; then mv $f $backupdir; restore=mv; else :; fi; \
	  done; \
	else :; fi && \
	cd "$am__cwd"; \
	if makeinfo --split-size=5000000 --split-size=5000000   -I ../../../bfd/doc \
	 -o ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info ../../../bfd/doc/bfd.texinfo; \
	then \
	  rc=0; \
	  cd ../../../bfd/doc; \
	else \
	  rc=$?; \
	  cd ../../../bfd/doc && \
	  $restore $backupdir/* `echo "./../../../bfd/doc/bfd.info" | sed 's|[^/]*$||'`; \
	fi; \
	rm -rf $backupdir; exit $rc

	  compiler="/AM/AM_tools/gcc-4.2.2/build-gcc/./gcc/xgcc -B/AM/AM_tools/gcc-4.2.2/build-gcc/./gcc/ -B/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/bin/ -B/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/lib/ -isystem /AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/include -isystem /AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/sys-include"; \

	    dir=`echo $i | sed -e 's/;.*$//'`; \

	      true; \
	    else \
	      if [ -d ../${dir}/${lib} ]; then \
		flags=`echo $i | sed -e 's/^[^;]*;//' -e 's/@/ -/g'`; \
		if (cd ../${dir}/${lib}; make "AR=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/bin/ar" "AR_FLAGS=rc" "CC=/AM/AM_tools/gcc-4.2.2/build-gcc/./gcc/xgcc -B/AM/AM_tools/gcc-4.2.2/build-gcc/./gcc/ -B/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/bin/ -B/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/lib/ -isystem /AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/include -isystem /AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/sys-include" "CFLAGS=-O2 -g -O2 " "DESTDIR=" "LIBCFLAGS=-O2 -g -O2 " "EXTRA_OFILES=" "HDEFINES=" "INSTALL=/usr/bin/install -c" "INSTALL_DATA=/usr/bin/install -c -m 644" "INSTALL_PROGRAM=/usr/bin/install -c" "LDFLAGS=" "LOADLIBES=" "RANLIB=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/bin/ranlib" "SHELL=/bin/sh" "prefix=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" "exec_prefix=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" "libdir=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/lib" "libsubdir=" "tooldir=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf" \
				CFLAGS="-O2 -g -O2  ${flags}" \
				CCASFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				FCFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				FFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				ADAFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				prefix="/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" \

				GCJFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				CXXFLAGS="-g -O2  ${flags}" \
				LIBCFLAGS="-O2 -g -O2  ${flags}" \
				LIBCXXFLAGS="-g -O2  -fno-implicit-templates ${flags}" \
				LDFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				MULTIFLAGS="${flags}" \
				DESTDIR="" \
				INSTALL="/usr/bin/install -c" \

	  compiler="brownie32-elf-gcc -B/AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/build-newlib/brownie32-elf/newlib/ -isystem /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/build-newlib/brownie32-elf/newlib/targ-include -isystem /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/newlib/libc/include"; \

if [ -z "b32-quickcall" ]; then \
	  true; \
	else \
	  rootpre=`${PWDCMD-pwd}`/; export rootpre; \
	  srcrootpre=`cd ../../../newlib; ${PWDCMD-pwd}`/; export srcrootpre; \
	  lib=`echo ${rootpre} | sed -e 's,^.*/\([^/][^/]*\)/$,\1,'`; \
	  compiler="brownie32-elf-gcc -B/AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/build-newlib/brownie32-elf/newlib/ -isystem /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/build-newlib/brownie32-elf/newlib/targ-include -isystem /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/newlib/libc/include"; \
	  for i in `${compiler} --print-multi-lib 2>/dev/null`; do \
	    dir=`echo $i | sed -e 's/;.*$//'`; \
	    if [ "${dir}" = "." ]; then \
	      true; \
	    else \
	      if [ -d ../${dir}/${lib} ]; then \
		flags=`echo $i | sed -e 's/^[^;]*;//' -e 's/@/ -/g'`; \
		if (cd ../${dir}/${lib}; make "AR_FLAGS=rc" 	"CC_FOR_BUILD=gcc" 	"CFLAGS=-O0 -gstabs -O0  " 	"CFLAGS_FOR_BUILD=-gstabs -O0 " 	"CFLAGS_FOR_TARGET=-O0 -gstabs -O0  " 	"LDFLAGS=" 	"LIBCFLAGS=-O0 -gstabs -O0  " 	"LIBCFLAGS_FOR_TARGET=-O0 -gstabs -O0  " 	"MAKE=make" 	"MAKEINFO=makeinfo --split-size=5000000 --split-size=5000000    " 	"PICFLAG=" 	"PICFLAG_FOR_TARGET=" 	"SHELL=/bin/sh" 	"EXPECT=expect" 	"RUNTEST=runtest" 	"RUNTESTFLAGS=" 	"exec_prefix=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" 	"infodir=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/info" 	"libdir=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/lib" 	"prefix=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" 	"tooldir=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf" 	"top_toollibdir=/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen/brownie32-elf/lib" 	"AR=brownie32-elf-ar" 	"AS=brownie32-elf-as" 	"CC=brownie32-elf-gcc -B/AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/build-newlib/brownie32-elf/newlib/ -isystem /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/build-newlib/brownie32-elf/newlib/targ-include -isystem /AM/AM_tools/newlib-1.14.0/newlib/libc/include" 	"LD=brownie32-elf-ld" 	"LIBCFLAGS=-O0 -gstabs -O0  " 	"NM=brownie32-elf-nm" 	"PICFLAG=" 	"RANLIB=brownie32-elf-ranlib" 	"DESTDIR=" \
				CFLAGS="-O0 -gstabs -O0   ${flags}" \
				FCFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				FFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				ADAFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				prefix="/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" \
				exec_prefix="/AM/package2/meister/browstd32.swgen" \
				GCJFLAGS="@GCJFLAGS@ ${flags}" \
				CXXFLAGS="-gstabs -O2  ${flags}" \
				LIBCFLAGS="-O0 -gstabs -O0   ${flags}" \
				LIBCXXFLAGS="-gstabs -O2  -fno-implicit-templates ${flags}" \
				LDFLAGS=" ${flags}" \
				MULTIFLAGS="${flags}" \
				DESTDIR="" \
				INSTALL="/usr/bin/install -c" \
				INSTALL_DATA="/usr/bin/install -c -m 644" \
				INSTALL_PROGRAM="/usr/bin/install -c " \
				INSTALL_SCRIPT="/usr/bin/install -c" \
				install); then \
		  true; \
		else \
		  exit 1; \
		fi; \
	      else true; \
	      fi; \
	    fi; \
	  done; \
	fi

Test: Setting up a Similar License Server like i80pc57 (CentOS-5)
====================================================================
Dear Hussain,
Good news!
I am happy to hear that node lock license works correctly.
Concerning to the floating license, could you please check
the following points again?
Server program was developed in the same environment
as other software, and the same environment as client is required.
1. Server system is not 64 bit OS, but 32 bit OS CentOS 5.
2. SELinux is disabled.
3. There is libcrypto.so.4 in /lib directory.
4. Location of License file correctly in server side is set.
In expanded ASIPLicServ directory, sample license startup
script named ASIPlicServ is included. In this file, license file location is set by envrioment variable LICENSE_FILE_PATH
In this sample script,
LICENSE_FILE_PATH=/usr/local/ASIPSLicServ/ASIPmeister_001.lic
Did you change the name and location of ASIPmeister145.lic?
5 Set license at the client side,
$ export ASIPS_LICENSE=29000@LICENSE_SERVER_NAME
BR.
Yoshinori Takeuchi











i80pc57 Hard Disk Controller damaged
====================================
Martin recovered all the OS from the HD.
Martin sugessted not to install CentOS5 as it is old and old libraries are not available. Also its risky in terms of security.
And we dont have old PC that supports CentOS5.
He installed i80pc57 on my system using a VM.


















Setting the Language
=================================================


https://ccollins.wordpress.com/2009da/01/06/how-to-change-date-formats-on-ubuntu/
[root@i80pc57 locales]# sudo cp en_US custom
[root@i80pc57 locales]# date
Wed Apr  5 18:04:32 CEST 2017
[root@i80pc57 locales]# sudo vim custom 
[root@i80pc57 locales]# sudo localedef -f UTF-8 -i custom custom.UTF-8
[root@i80pc57 locales]# LC_TIME="custom.UTF-8"
[root@i80pc57 locales]# date
20170405
[root@i80pc57 locales]# . /usr/local/ASIPSLicServ/ASIPmeister.setup 
[root@i80pc57 locales]# ASIPmeister
[root@i80pc57 locales]# 
=====================================================
